Defective baby recliners are being recalled – but only after killing five infants.The U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) announced Friday a voluntary recall of the killer Nap Nanny and Nap Nanny Chill recliners and covers, according to a filing posted on the agency’s website. The recall is part of a settlement reached last year with Baby Matters, the recliners’ distributor, the filing states.“CPSC urges consumers to immediately stop use of all Nap Nanny and Nap Nanny Chill recliners,” the filing urges customers.

