Widely sold across the US, the products have injured at least 92 babies - based on complaints filed with the agency - as a result of them hanging and/or falling out of them, according to the filing. Some of the injured even included babies properly restrained in the faulty products’ harness, the filing continued.

Four infants died in the Nap Nanny Generation Two recliners, a fifth died in the Chill model, according to the filing. Roughly 165,000 of the baby suffocating models were sold between 2009 and 2013, with parents paying about $130 for the privilege of endangering their beloved newborns, the filing stated.With Baby Matters out of business, the agency urges those who bought their products to return them to retailers for a refund.

