The products were already voluntarily recalled at the end of 2012 by Amazon.com, Babies R Us, Buy Buy Baby, Diapers.com, and Toys R Us. Consumers purchasing the items from other retailers have been urged “to immediately dispose of the products to ensure that they are not used again,” by the agency.The original recall came as a result of the CPSC filing a complaint against Baby Matters in response to consumer complaints over the danger they posed to infants, according to the filing.

